Text.SourceString: Yes? May I help you?//<portrait=happy>My name’s <NPCName>Luke</>. Pleasure is mine.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes? May I help you?//<portrait=happy>My name’s <NPCName>Luke</>. Pleasure is mine.

Text.SourceString: Interesting. Moving to a small island from Pokyo is an odd choice.//<portrait=normal>And why now? But I suppose everyone has their own reasons.//Good luck with everything.
Text.LocalizedString: Interesting. Moving to a small island from Pokyo is an odd choice.//<portrait=normal>And why now? But I suppose everyone has their own reasons.//Good luck with everything.

Text.SourceString: I don’t get why Mother keeps complaining about the recycling center. I walked past it yesterday, and it smelled fine.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t get why Mother keeps complaining about the recycling center. I walked past it yesterday, and it smelled fine.

Text.SourceString: I don't mind chipping in a tad extra in taxes if it goes directly towards sprucing up the buildings around here.//<portrait=concerned>But that’s not always the case, and regrettably, I don't see eye to eye with some of this town's current spending.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't mind chipping in a tad extra in taxes if it goes directly towards sprucing up the buildings around here.//<portrait=concerned>But that’s not always the case, and regrettably, I don't see eye to eye with some of this town's current spending.

Text.SourceString: The seasonal decorations, for instance.//I reckon we don't need to be splashing any more of the budget on that.
Text.LocalizedString: The seasonal decorations, for instance.//I reckon we don't need to be splashing any more of the budget on that.

Text.SourceString: I read people in an earlier civilization here used to farm together and share their harvest.//It was the law of the land.
Text.LocalizedString: I read people in an earlier civilization here used to farm together and share their harvest.//It was the law of the land.

Text.SourceString: It probably worked because it was a much simpler time back then.//<portrait=normal>Nowadays, I reckon we'd be needing some sort of permit even for running something as basic as a community garden.//Ponderous, isn't it?
Text.LocalizedString: It probably worked because it was a much simpler time back then.//<portrait=normal>Nowadays, I reckon we'd be needing some sort of permit even for running something as basic as a community garden.//Ponderous, isn't it?

Text.SourceString: I wouldn’t be much use gardening. I learned a thing or two from Mother, but I have no, umm… What do they call it?
Text.LocalizedString: I wouldn’t be much use gardening. I learned a thing or two from Mother, but I have no, umm… What do they call it?

Text.SourceString: Ah, yes. I don't possess what they call a "green thumb."//No talent for growing plants, I'm afraid.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, yes. I don't possess what they call a "green thumb."//No talent for growing plants, I'm afraid.

Text.SourceString: I used to work on Mondays, but there wasn’t much business.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to work on Mondays, but there wasn’t much business.

Text.SourceString: People are too busy to shop at the beginning of the week, I suppose. So, here I am.
Text.LocalizedString: People are too busy to shop at the beginning of the week, I suppose. So, here I am.

Text.SourceString: The weather is nice today. I should do something, like go to the beach.//<portrait=sad>Feels like a waste otherwise.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather is nice today. I should do something, like go to the beach.//<portrait=sad>Feels like a waste otherwise.

Text.SourceString: But I won’t. Well, technically speaking, it's more like I can't.//<portrait=concerned>I've got work piled up that'll keep me busy for at least the next two or three days, you see.
Text.LocalizedString: But I won’t. Well, technically speaking, it's more like I can't.//<portrait=concerned>I've got work piled up that'll keep me busy for at least the next two or three days, you see.

Text.SourceString: Shopping day? Tuesdays are when people usually shop and submit their orders.
Text.LocalizedString: Shopping day? Tuesdays are when people usually shop and submit their orders.

Text.SourceString: Have you seen the new items I have in stock?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen the new items I have in stock?

Text.SourceString: You can see my commercial on TV every other day. But I usually only add new stock on weekends.
Text.LocalizedString: You can see my commercial on TV every other day. But I usually only add new stock on weekends.

Text.SourceString: Not always, though. Might want to keep that in mind.
Text.LocalizedString: Not always, though. Might want to keep that in mind.

Text.SourceString: Blimey, you've got quite a style, I must say.
Text.LocalizedString: Blimey, you've got quite a style, I must say.

Text.SourceString: It’s distinctive, to say the least.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s distinctive, to say the least.

Text.SourceString: I reckon I'll change up me display today.
Text.LocalizedString: I reckon I'll change up me display today.

Text.SourceString: How’s your week been so far? You look like you haven’t slept much.
Text.LocalizedString: How’s your week been so far? You look like you haven’t slept much.

Text.SourceString: My store is closed tomorrow. I usually do some bookkeeping at home instead.
Text.LocalizedString: My store is closed tomorrow. I usually do some bookkeeping at home instead.

Text.SourceString: I don’t fancy fishing. You just sit around doing nothing for a long time, waiting for a fish to take the bait.//Doesn’t seem productive to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t fancy fishing. You just sit around doing nothing for a long time, waiting for a fish to take the bait.//Doesn’t seem productive to me.

Text.SourceString: All that waitin' around...all for a fish. One fish.//Yeah, can't be bothered with that.
Text.LocalizedString: All that waitin' around...all for a fish. One fish.//Yeah, can't be bothered with that.

Text.SourceString: Aren’t you supposed to be working?
Text.LocalizedString: Aren’t you supposed to be working?

Text.SourceString: I’m both for and against taking breaks from work.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m both for and against taking breaks from work.

Text.SourceString: I reckon it's equally important to work hard and understand our limits.
Text.LocalizedString: I reckon it's equally important to work hard and understand our limits.

Text.SourceString: Hello! How are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Hello! How are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Taco</> is my dog. He followed <NpcName>Suki</> out of the forest and has rather made himself at home here, hasn't he?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</> is my dog. He followed <NpcName>Suki</> out of the forest and has rather made himself at home here, hasn't he?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Taco</> likes to roam around on his own, a bona fide explorer, one might say.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</> likes to roam around on his own, a bona fide explorer, one might say.

Text.SourceString: Oh, good Goddess! What happened to you? Did you get attacked?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, good Goddess! What happened to you? Did you get attacked?

Text.SourceString: Oh, good! I just never really know with you, I guess.//You always seem to maintain a rather, shall we say, relaxed appearance.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, good! I just never really know with you, I guess.//You always seem to maintain a rather, shall we say, relaxed appearance.

Text.SourceString: I shall take things at a leisurely pace today.
Text.LocalizedString: I shall take things at a leisurely pace today.

Text.SourceString: Are you submitting an order?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you submitting an order?

Text.SourceString: No obligation, mind you, but I dare say you should.
Text.LocalizedString: No obligation, mind you, but I dare say you should.

Text.SourceString: Has anyone ever told you that you talk a lot? It’s a bit counterproductive when you’re trying to work.
Text.LocalizedString: Has anyone ever told you that you talk a lot? It’s a bit counterproductive when you’re trying to work.

Text.SourceString: I can never decide on my favorite grape. I want to say yuscat because you can both eat it and turn it into wine.
Text.LocalizedString: I can never decide on my favorite grape. I want to say yuscat because you can both eat it and turn it into wine.

Text.SourceString: But does that mean my decision is based merely on convenience? Would I change my mind if, perhaps, I took flavor into account?//<portrait=sad>I need to think about this.
Text.LocalizedString: But does that mean my decision is based merely on convenience? Would I change my mind if, perhaps, I took flavor into account?//<portrait=sad>I need to think about this.

Text.SourceString: They just increased the price of ads. Again! Unbelievable.
Text.LocalizedString: They just increased the price of ads. Again! Unbelievable.

Text.SourceString: How am I expected to turn a profit? I can't possibly increase my rates.//The townies wouldn't be able to afford my goods if I hiked up the prices.//<portrait=concerned>I'd risk alienating customers, which could very well drive me out of business.
Text.LocalizedString: How am I expected to turn a profit? I can't possibly increase my rates.//The townies wouldn't be able to afford my goods if I hiked up the prices.//<portrait=concerned>I'd risk alienating customers, which could very well drive me out of business.

Text.SourceString: I might go to the beach tomorrow. Visit the shack or something of the sort.
Text.LocalizedString: I might go to the beach tomorrow. Visit the shack or something of the sort.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. I should wear a hat.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. I should wear a hat.

Text.SourceString: Running errands, are we?
Text.LocalizedString: Running errands, are we?

Text.SourceString: Your boots are dirty, by the way. Perhaps one of these days, you could go by the creek and clean them.
Text.LocalizedString: Your boots are dirty, by the way. Perhaps one of these days, you could go by the creek and clean them.

Text.SourceString: Only if you want to. You certainly don’t have to.//But judging by the state of your boots, you already know that.
Text.LocalizedString: Only if you want to. You certainly don’t have to.//But judging by the state of your boots, you already know that.

Text.SourceString: Ugh. I did it again. Sorry if I sounded condescending. I didn’t mean to.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh. I did it again. Sorry if I sounded condescending. I didn’t mean to.

Text.SourceString: Do you have a favorite grape?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have a favorite grape?

Text.SourceString: You seem surprised. Why? Did I startle you?
Text.LocalizedString: You seem surprised. Why? Did I startle you?

Text.SourceString: I can never decide on my favorite grape. I want to say yuscat because you can both eat it and turn it into wine.
Text.LocalizedString: I can never decide on my favorite grape. I want to say yuscat because you can both eat it and turn it into wine.

Text.SourceString: But does that mean my decision is based merely on convenience? Would I change my mind if, perhaps, I took flavor into account?
Text.LocalizedString: But does that mean my decision is based merely on convenience? Would I change my mind if, perhaps, I took flavor into account?

Text.SourceString: I need to think about this.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to think about this.

Text.SourceString: I have to ship out tons of wine from the vineyard tomorrow at dawn.//I've sorted the paperwork today, and hopefully, the boat will arrive on schedule.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to ship out tons of wine from the vineyard tomorrow at dawn.//I've sorted the paperwork today, and hopefully, the boat will arrive on schedule.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. I might need to order some extra TVs to sell. They seem to be flying off the shelves.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. I might need to order some extra TVs to sell. They seem to be flying off the shelves.

Text.SourceString: TVs are expensive to stock, though. I’m not quite sure what to do. I've noticed people tend to buy more when I have tellies on display.//<portrait=sad>The trouble is I don’t have actual data to back up my theory.
Text.LocalizedString: TVs are expensive to stock, though. I’m not quite sure what to do. I've noticed people tend to buy more when I have tellies on display.//<portrait=sad>The trouble is I don’t have actual data to back up my theory.

Text.SourceString: I just got this cool speaker in this week’s shipment.//I’m going to test it out at <NpcName>Pablo’s</> and see if I should keep it or not.
Text.LocalizedString: I just got this cool speaker in this week’s shipment.//I’m going to test it out at <NpcName>Pablo’s</> and see if I should keep it or not.

Text.SourceString: I've got a no-return policy at Socket. My supplier only guarantees my personal orders.//Even then, it’s limited to tellies and speakers, not kitchen appliances.
Text.LocalizedString: I've got a no-return policy at Socket. My supplier only guarantees my personal orders.//Even then, it’s limited to tellies and speakers, not kitchen appliances.

Text.SourceString: I let my hair grow out once, and it was awfully hot.
Text.LocalizedString: I let my hair grow out once, and it was awfully hot.

Text.SourceString: Not that it looked smashing. I mean “hot” as in body temperature.//<portrait=annoyed>It had me sweating buckets.
Text.LocalizedString: Not that it looked smashing. I mean “hot” as in body temperature.//<portrait=annoyed>It had me sweating buckets.

Text.SourceString: My weekend plans? Hmm. Good question.
Text.LocalizedString: My weekend plans? Hmm. Good question.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know yet. I suppose it depends on how many orders I have to sort out today.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know yet. I suppose it depends on how many orders I have to sort out today.

Text.SourceString: It’s a pickle deciding on gifts.//How do you know someone’s tastes haven’t shifted since the last time you gave them a present?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a pickle deciding on gifts.//How do you know someone’s tastes haven’t shifted since the last time you gave them a present?

Text.SourceString: My personal go-to gift is a meal from the Tavern.//If folks don’t like that, it’s nothing personal, right?
Text.LocalizedString: My personal go-to gift is a meal from the Tavern.//If folks don’t like that, it’s nothing personal, right?

Text.SourceString: I was reading at the library the other day, minding my own business, and somebody tapped me on the shoulder.
Text.LocalizedString: I was reading at the library the other day, minding my own business, and somebody tapped me on the shoulder.

Text.SourceString: I was reading. At the library. Isn’t that a clear sign I don’t want to be disturbed?//Some of us need to learn to read the room a bit better.
Text.LocalizedString: I was reading. At the library. Isn’t that a clear sign I don’t want to be disturbed?//Some of us need to learn to read the room a bit better.

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to startle you, but I’ve got to tell you about this book.//<portrait=surprised>It reckons a bunch of different magical creatures used to dwell on this island.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to startle you, but I’ve got to tell you about this book.//<portrait=surprised>It reckons a bunch of different magical creatures used to dwell on this island.

Text.SourceString: I mean, maybe there was a Goddess. But merfolk?//Not just a few merfolk, but a whole population. It claims an ancient kingdom of merfolk lived around Coral Island. Huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I mean, maybe there was a Goddess. But merfolk?//Not just a few merfolk, but a whole population. It claims an ancient kingdom of merfolk lived around Coral Island. Huh?

Text.SourceString: I’m not one to care about farming or to poke around in other people’s personal lives.//But how are things with you and your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not one to care about farming or to poke around in other people’s personal lives.//But how are things with you and your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I like the sound of that!
Text.LocalizedString: I like the sound of that!

Special.SourceString: It’s going well. Plant, harvest, ka-ching!
Special.LocalizedString: It’s going well. Plant, harvest, ka-ching!

68.SpecialTag: It’s going well. Plant, harvest, ka-ching!
68.Question: R1

Text.SourceString: It was literal trash. This is ridiculous!
Text.LocalizedString: It was literal trash. This is ridiculous!

Text.SourceString: So sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. That’s so sad.
Text.LocalizedString: So sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. That’s so sad.

Special.SourceString: It's not good. I’m nose-diving into bankruptcy.
Special.LocalizedString: It's not good. I’m nose-diving into bankruptcy.

70.SpecialTag: It's not good. I’m nose-diving into bankruptcy.
70.Question: R3

Text.SourceString: Lamps and blenders? Is that all I am to this island?//Everyone just sees me as the bloke who sells lamps and blenders.
Text.LocalizedString: Lamps and blenders? Is that all I am to this island?//Everyone just sees me as the bloke who sells lamps and blenders.

Text.SourceString: Not my parents, though. To them, I’m the wine merchant.//<portrait=normal>I’m the one making sure their winery turns a profit. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: Not my parents, though. To them, I’m the wine merchant.//<portrait=normal>I’m the one making sure their winery turns a profit. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: It’s a jolly day, for sure. And I shall treat it as such. I’m done complaining for the week.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a jolly day, for sure. And I shall treat it as such. I’m done complaining for the week.

Text.SourceString: It’s lively here on Saturday, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s lively here on Saturday, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I’m feeling a little antsy. I think I’m just ready for Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m feeling a little antsy. I think I’m just ready for Summer.

Text.SourceString: This year’s Consumer Electronics Expo was amazing. Too bad I could only stream it.//I wasn’t able to get tickets.
Text.LocalizedString: This year’s Consumer Electronics Expo was amazing. Too bad I could only stream it.//I wasn’t able to get tickets.

Text.SourceString: It’s always cool to see new technology. That’s why the Consumer Electronics Expo is the <Italic>one</> event I’m looking forward to in Spring.//<portrait=concerned>Well, that’s not true. I also like the Cherry Blossom Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s always cool to see new technology. That’s why the Consumer Electronics Expo is the <Italic>one</> event I’m looking forward to in Spring.//<portrait=concerned>Well, that’s not true. I also like the Cherry Blossom Festival.

Text.SourceString: One of the coolest things I saw at the Consumer Electronics Expo has to be self-driving cars. When they were first introduced.//I thought it was groundbreaking. Hmm.
Text.LocalizedString: One of the coolest things I saw at the Consumer Electronics Expo has to be self-driving cars. When they were first introduced.//I thought it was groundbreaking. Hmm.

Text.SourceString: The smart bathtub was amazing too. You set your preferred temperature, and it does everything for you.//It fills up, makes sure the temperature is spot on, and drains automatically when you're done.
Text.LocalizedString: The smart bathtub was amazing too. You set your preferred temperature, and it does everything for you.//It fills up, makes sure the temperature is spot on, and drains automatically when you're done.

Text.SourceString: Spring is like the start of the life cycle for electronics, much like many things in life and nature. It's when new gizmos are launched to the market.//<portrait=happy>Exciting time for farmers too, I suppose. With the going back to farming and all.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring is like the start of the life cycle for electronics, much like many things in life and nature. It's when new gizmos are launched to the market.//<portrait=happy>Exciting time for farmers too, I suppose. With the going back to farming and all.

Text.SourceString: I know it's Summer, but I can't be bothered to put on shorts.//I live on a hill behind a vineyard. If I wore shorts, I’d get eaten alive by mosquitoes.
Text.LocalizedString: I know it's Summer, but I can't be bothered to put on shorts.//I live on a hill behind a vineyard. If I wore shorts, I’d get eaten alive by mosquitoes.

Text.SourceString: There's no exciting news about electronics in the Summer. All that happened in Spring.//Let’s wait and see what the reviews say!
Text.LocalizedString: There's no exciting news about electronics in the Summer. All that happened in Spring.//Let’s wait and see what the reviews say!

Text.SourceString: I have to say I'm quite enjoying Summer more than I anticipated, even with the bugs and all.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to say I'm quite enjoying Summer more than I anticipated, even with the bugs and all.

Text.SourceString: What is it about Summer that makes me fancy picking up my golf clubs?//<portrait=normal>Must be all those Summer camps my parents sent me to, I reckon. The memories stick.
Text.LocalizedString: What is it about Summer that makes me fancy picking up my golf clubs?//<portrait=normal>Must be all those Summer camps my parents sent me to, I reckon. The memories stick.

Text.SourceString: The town is lively in Summer.//I quite like it.
Text.LocalizedString: The town is lively in Summer.//I quite like it.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Nina</> and I used to go sailing with our fathers every Summer. We stopped because her father…//<portrait=sad>Well, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Nina</> and I used to go sailing with our fathers every Summer. We stopped because her father…//<portrait=sad>Well, you know.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I’ve seen Father sailing since I was a boy. I haven’t gone in a while either.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I should ask him.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I’ve seen Father sailing since I was a boy. I haven’t gone in a while either.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I should ask him.

Text.SourceString: People who think tomato soup is best in Fall are completely off their rocker.//<portrait=normal>Tomatoes are a Summer crop and therefore best enjoyed in Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: People who think tomato soup is best in Fall are completely off their rocker.//<portrait=normal>Tomatoes are a Summer crop and therefore best enjoyed in Summer.

Text.SourceString: What did you do in Summer when you were a kid?
Text.LocalizedString: What did you do in Summer when you were a kid?

Text.SourceString: You can sleep in other seasons as well, you know. But I see your point.//I used to go to camps abroad. Sometimes, sleeping in wasn’t part of the package. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: You can sleep in other seasons as well, you know. But I see your point.//I used to go to camps abroad. Sometimes, sleeping in wasn’t part of the package. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: I did that too. Sailing was nice. The sea is one of my favorite places to be.//And tennis camp was fun. You’re gone for a whole season and come back improved by the time school starts.
Text.LocalizedString: I did that too. Sailing was nice. The sea is one of my favorite places to be.//And tennis camp was fun. You’re gone for a whole season and come back improved by the time school starts.

Text.SourceString: Yes, I did as well, in between Summer camps.//Unfortunately, some of them, like the tennis camp in San Franciskyo, didn’t let us bring any games.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes, I did as well, in between Summer camps.//Unfortunately, some of them, like the tennis camp in San Franciskyo, didn’t let us bring any games.

Text.SourceString: I wish I could spend more time at Socket, but it's harvest season, and the vineyard is just taking up all of my time.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could spend more time at Socket, but it's harvest season, and the vineyard is just taking up all of my time.

Text.SourceString: Are you as busy as we are in Fall?//<portrait=concerned>It’s honestly such a pain. But it is what it is.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you as busy as we are in Fall?//<portrait=concerned>It’s honestly such a pain. But it is what it is.

Text.SourceString: I need to make sure we have enough time to process and ship orders before Winter hits.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to make sure we have enough time to process and ship orders before Winter hits.

Text.SourceString: We do have a greenhouse where we grow grapes, but the taste never quite matches the grapes we harvest in Fall.//That’s just my personal opinion.
Text.LocalizedString: We do have a greenhouse where we grow grapes, but the taste never quite matches the grapes we harvest in Fall.//That’s just my personal opinion.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been knee-deep in reviews of this year’s Consumer Electronics Expo.//Definitely looking forward to the online end-of-year sale. There are things I’d like to get my hands on.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been knee-deep in reviews of this year’s Consumer Electronics Expo.//Definitely looking forward to the online end-of-year sale. There are things I’d like to get my hands on.

Text.SourceString: I go to a small electronics store in Tosaka. It has lots of things I need.//You can check out their speakers from low end to high end. That way, you can compare them for yourself right there and then.//Size doesn’t matter when it comes to electronics stores.
Text.LocalizedString: I go to a small electronics store in Tosaka. It has lots of things I need.//You can check out their speakers from low end to high end. That way, you can compare them for yourself right there and then.//Size doesn’t matter when it comes to electronics stores.

Text.SourceString: Are you warm in those, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I reckon the jumper I’m wearing is sufficient for Fall. No need for heavy coats just yet.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you warm in those, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I reckon the jumper I’m wearing is sufficient for Fall. No need for heavy coats just yet.

Text.SourceString: If you need more layers for Winter, White Flamingo usually has great jumpers.//I get mine from there. Sometimes they have questionable things, though, like giant animal onesies.//Fashion, I suppose. I don’t quite understand.
Text.LocalizedString: If you need more layers for Winter, White Flamingo usually has great jumpers.//I get mine from there. Sometimes they have questionable things, though, like giant animal onesies.//Fashion, I suppose. I don’t quite understand.

Text.SourceString: Phew, things have finally slowed down at the winery.//Mother can take care of the greenhouse, and all that’s left is filling orders and doing paperwork. Simple.
Text.LocalizedString: Phew, things have finally slowed down at the winery.//Mother can take care of the greenhouse, and all that’s left is filling orders and doing paperwork. Simple.

Text.SourceString: Are you coming to Mother’s party?//<portrait=happy>You should. We usually have an amazing spread and fun games all night.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you coming to Mother’s party?//<portrait=happy>You should. We usually have an amazing spread and fun games all night.

Text.SourceString: Now that it’s Winter, there are massive electronics sales everywhere!//I might check out the electronics district in Pokyo. Let’s see how the week goes!
Text.LocalizedString: Now that it’s Winter, there are massive electronics sales everywhere!//I might check out the electronics district in Pokyo. Let’s see how the week goes!

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait for the Consumer Electronics Expo this Spring.//I wonder what <Italic>weird</> stuff they’ll have!
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait for the Consumer Electronics Expo this Spring.//I wonder what <Italic>weird</> stuff they’ll have!

Text.SourceString: I’m so glad Fall is over and done with. Now I can put more energy into Socket.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so glad Fall is over and done with. Now I can put more energy into Socket.

Text.SourceString: We do grow grapes in the greenhouse in Winter, but we don’t rely too much on them.//They’re sort of like a backup supply.
Text.LocalizedString: We do grow grapes in the greenhouse in Winter, but we don’t rely too much on them.//They’re sort of like a backup supply.

Text.SourceString: Shouldn’t you start farming or something?
Text.LocalizedString: Shouldn’t you start farming or something?

Text.SourceString: If you need to buy seeds, go to <NPCName>Sam</>’s General Store.//He carries a variety.
Text.LocalizedString: If you need to buy seeds, go to <NPCName>Sam</>’s General Store.//He carries a variety.

Text.SourceString: Pufferfish Corporation owns that building, you know.//We found out last Fall when we tried to lease the building for our tasting room.
Text.LocalizedString: Pufferfish Corporation owns that building, you know.//We found out last Fall when we tried to lease the building for our tasting room.

Text.SourceString: They rejected our offer without any explanation. Now we know why.
Text.LocalizedString: They rejected our offer without any explanation. Now we know why.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know about Pokyo, but deep-fried bananas are a thing around here. <NPCName>Joko</> loves them.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know about Pokyo, but deep-fried bananas are a thing around here. <NPCName>Joko</> loves them.

Text.SourceString: There are plenty of flowers around. You can find tulips and violets around the lake if that’s your thing.
Text.LocalizedString: There are plenty of flowers around. You can find tulips and violets around the lake if that’s your thing.

Text.SourceString: How do you even choose which ones to pick?
Text.LocalizedString: How do you even choose which ones to pick?

Text.SourceString: Did you do anything fun to celebrate the New Year?
Text.LocalizedString: Did you do anything fun to celebrate the New Year?

Text.SourceString: Tomorrow is the Cherry Blossom Festival. It’s probably the highlight of the year on Coral Island.
Text.LocalizedString: Tomorrow is the Cherry Blossom Festival. It’s probably the highlight of the year on Coral Island.

Text.SourceString: That was a bold statement, wasn’t it? Well, I think it’s true.
Text.LocalizedString: That was a bold statement, wasn’t it? Well, I think it’s true.

Text.SourceString: It’s nearly the end of Spring already. I feel like I haven’t done much.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nearly the end of Spring already. I feel like I haven’t done much.

Text.SourceString: People tend to buy more outdoor grills this time of year. Maybe they’re getting ready for Summer cookouts.
Text.LocalizedString: People tend to buy more outdoor grills this time of year. Maybe they’re getting ready for Summer cookouts.

Text.SourceString: That wasn’t a wild guess.//I looked at the sales numbers. Well, in any case, it’s good for business.
Text.LocalizedString: That wasn’t a wild guess.//I looked at the sales numbers. Well, in any case, it’s good for business.

Text.SourceString: I guess this’ll be the last week we can enjoy the cherry blossoms this year.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess this’ll be the last week we can enjoy the cherry blossoms this year.

Text.SourceString: Cherry blossoms are so beautiful, yet their lives are so tragically short. Perhaps like life…
Text.LocalizedString: Cherry blossoms are so beautiful, yet their lives are so tragically short. Perhaps like life…

Text.SourceString: That was a song lyric, wasn’t it?//From the Shell Rockers? I love that band.
Text.LocalizedString: That was a song lyric, wasn’t it?//From the Shell Rockers? I love that band.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Luke</> hums a sad song by the Shell Rockers.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Luke</> hums a sad song by the Shell Rockers.]

Text.SourceString: Blimey, it's the first week of Summer and the mosquitoes are out in full force already.
Text.LocalizedString: Blimey, it's the first week of Summer and the mosquitoes are out in full force already.

Text.SourceString: Huh. I feel like you’ve asked me that already.//<portrait=normal>In any case, I find star fruit aesthetically pleasing, but a tad too bitter for my taste.
Text.LocalizedString: Huh. I feel like you’ve asked me that already.//<portrait=normal>In any case, I find star fruit aesthetically pleasing, but a tad too bitter for my taste.

Text.SourceString: Why are you so keen about star fruit?
Text.LocalizedString: Why are you so keen about star fruit?

Text.SourceString: We’re cleaning up the beach next Saturday, <PlayerName>$player</>. Come prepared!
Text.LocalizedString: We’re cleaning up the beach next Saturday, <PlayerName>$player</>. Come prepared!

Text.SourceString: We have a duty to look after Mother Nature. If we don’t, then who will?
Text.LocalizedString: We have a duty to look after Mother Nature. If we don’t, then who will?

Text.SourceString: Can't believe next week's already Fall.
Text.LocalizedString: Can't believe next week's already Fall.

Text.SourceString: It’s still baking hot! Doesn't seem to cool down one bit.//<portrait=normal>Or is it just me?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s still baking hot! Doesn't seem to cool down one bit.//<portrait=normal>Or is it just me?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Nina</> and I used to hunt ghosts when we were nine or ten years old.//On windy nights, we got to stay up and eat ramen outside her villa.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Nina</> and I used to hunt ghosts when we were nine or ten years old.//On windy nights, we got to stay up and eat ramen outside her villa.

Text.SourceString: Her parents were okay with it. Our families are very close. Ah, fun times.
Text.LocalizedString: Her parents were okay with it. Our families are very close. Ah, fun times.

Text.SourceString: It’s the new season! I have new items in stock.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the new season! I have new items in stock.

Text.SourceString: How do you keep warm in your cabin on Fall nights?
Text.LocalizedString: How do you keep warm in your cabin on Fall nights?

Text.SourceString: I have some heater recommendations, if you’d like.
Text.LocalizedString: I have some heater recommendations, if you’d like.

Text.SourceString: I ordered some heaters for the ranch, and they still haven’t arrived. Disaster!
Text.LocalizedString: I ordered some heaters for the ranch, and they still haven’t arrived. Disaster!

Text.SourceString: Winter is around the corner. This is unprofessional! I should give them a ring.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is around the corner. This is unprofessional! I should give them a ring.

Text.SourceString: Look at how much snow has accumulated, and we’re not even a week into Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Look at how much snow has accumulated, and we’re not even a week into Winter.

Text.SourceString: So, what are you going to do for the next three or four weeks, seeing as you can’t farm much?
Text.LocalizedString: So, what are you going to do for the next three or four weeks, seeing as you can’t farm much?

Text.SourceString: The vineyard will rely on the greenhouse. Our production is declining. But it’s on purpose.
Text.LocalizedString: The vineyard will rely on the greenhouse. Our production is declining. But it’s on purpose.

Text.SourceString: I’m always intrigued by the things <NPCName>Ben</> manages to find on his Fall escapades.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m always intrigued by the things <NPCName>Ben</> manages to find on his Fall escapades.

Text.SourceString: Have you checked them out? They’re fascinating, to say the least.//<portrait=normal>One time, I saw a puppet made out of wood with a coconut shell for a head. It was all dressed up. Very odd.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you checked them out? They’re fascinating, to say the least.//<portrait=normal>One time, I saw a puppet made out of wood with a coconut shell for a head. It was all dressed up. Very odd.

Text.SourceString: Excited for the New Year?
Text.LocalizedString: Excited for the New Year?

Text.SourceString: Yeah, my family has a New Year’s Eve dinner tradition.//So, if nothing else comes up, we’ll probably just spend the day preparing for that.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, my family has a New Year’s Eve dinner tradition.//So, if nothing else comes up, we’ll probably just spend the day preparing for that.

Text.SourceString: Mother once told me that after I marry, she wants me to continue the family tradition, and she still expects me to spend New Year’s Eve with her, wherever I end up.
Text.LocalizedString: Mother once told me that after I marry, she wants me to continue the family tradition, and she still expects me to spend New Year’s Eve with her, wherever I end up.

Text.SourceString: I don’t care much about it, but it seems important to her. So, I’ll keep it up. At the end of the day, it’s the least I can do after everything my parents have done for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t care much about it, but it seems important to her. So, I’ll keep it up. At the end of the day, it’s the least I can do after everything my parents have done for me.

Text.SourceString: I hope you’re going to the New Year’s Eve dinner at the vineyard.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you’re going to the New Year’s Eve dinner at the vineyard.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind the rain.

Text.SourceString: Well, I actually do, a little.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I actually do, a little.

Text.SourceString: It depends, I guess. I don’t mind it today.
Text.LocalizedString: It depends, I guess. I don’t mind it today.

Text.SourceString: This rain isn’t that bad. It’s not too windy, and it’s not pouring.//It’s sprinkling, but not raining so heavily that I have to wear my rubber boots.
Text.LocalizedString: This rain isn’t that bad. It’s not too windy, and it’s not pouring.//It’s sprinkling, but not raining so heavily that I have to wear my rubber boots.

Text.SourceString: I feel a bit gloomy today.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel a bit gloomy today.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind the rain.

Text.SourceString: Well, you know what, <PlayerName>$player</>? I actually <Italic>do</> mind the rain a little.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, you know what, <PlayerName>$player</>? I actually <Italic>do</> mind the rain a little.

Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind the rain today.

Text.LocalizedString: It isn’t too windy, and it isn’t pouring. It’s sprinkling, but not raining so hard that I have to put my rubber boots on.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like storms.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like storms.

Text.SourceString: They scare me a little.
Text.LocalizedString: They scare me a little.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like storms.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like storms.

Text.SourceString: They scare me a little.
Text.LocalizedString: They scare me a little.

Text.SourceString: Excuse me. I’m kind of in a rush.
Text.LocalizedString: Excuse me. I’m kind of in a rush.

Text.SourceString: Excuse me. I’m kind of in a rush.
Text.LocalizedString: Excuse me. I’m kind of in a rush.

Text.SourceString: Do you have any cousins you’re close to, <PlayerName>$player</>?//For some reason, snowy days always remind me of my cousins and that one eccentric uncle.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have any cousins you’re close to, <PlayerName>$player</>?//For some reason, snowy days always remind me of my cousins and that one eccentric uncle.

Text.SourceString: Do you have one of those too?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have one of those too?

Text.SourceString: I have two. One from each side of the family. Lucky me.
Text.LocalizedString: I have two. One from each side of the family. Lucky me.

Text.SourceString: You have snow on your clothes.
Text.LocalizedString: You have snow on your clothes.

Text.SourceString: Do you have any cousins you’re close to, <PlayerName>$player</>?//For some reason, snowy days always remind me of my cousins and that one eccentric uncle.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have any cousins you’re close to, <PlayerName>$player</>?//For some reason, snowy days always remind me of my cousins and that one eccentric uncle.

Text.LocalizedString: Do you have one of those too?

Text.SourceString: I have two. One from each side of the family. Lucky me.
Text.LocalizedString: I have two. One from each side of the family. Lucky me.

Text.SourceString: One time, I found an onyx lying around in my cash register drawer. I gave it to <NpcName>Rafael</>, and he was thrilled.
Text.LocalizedString: One time, I found an onyx lying around in my cash register drawer. I gave it to <NpcName>Rafael</>, and he was thrilled.

Text.SourceString: Eh, I had no use for it, anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: Eh, I had no use for it, anyway.

Text.SourceString: Do you have any cousins you’re close to, <PlayerName>$player</>?//For some reason, snowy days always remind me of my cousins and that one eccentric uncle.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have any cousins you’re close to, <PlayerName>$player</>?//For some reason, snowy days always remind me of my cousins and that one eccentric uncle.

Text.LocalizedString: Do you have one of those too?

Text.SourceString: I have two. One from each side of the family. Lucky me.
Text.LocalizedString: I have two. One from each side of the family. Lucky me.

Text.SourceString: I can feel the snow through my sweater, straight to my bones.
Text.LocalizedString: I can feel the snow through my sweater, straight to my bones.

Text.SourceString: I should have stayed home today.
Text.LocalizedString: I should have stayed home today.

Text.SourceString: I always bring lunch from home.
Text.LocalizedString: I always bring lunch from home.

Text.SourceString: People ask a lot of questions without reading the user manual first.
Text.LocalizedString: People ask a lot of questions without reading the user manual first.

Text.SourceString: Why would they think I have better information than the literal user manual?
Text.LocalizedString: Why would they think I have better information than the literal user manual?

Text.SourceString: Oh, hey, submitting an order?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hey, submitting an order?

Text.SourceString: I’m probably just going to eat lunch in front of my computer and get things done.//No plans.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m probably just going to eat lunch in front of my computer and get things done.//No plans.

Text.SourceString: Just some green salad. Nothing fancy.//With herbed tempeh and lemon dressing.
Text.LocalizedString: Just some green salad. Nothing fancy.//With herbed tempeh and lemon dressing.

Text.SourceString: Oh, blimey! I forgot to close my bedroom door.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, blimey! I forgot to close my bedroom door.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Taco</> is going to make a huge mess in there. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</> is going to make a huge mess in there. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: Looking for my father? Hmm. I honestly don’t know where he might be.
Text.LocalizedString: Looking for my father? Hmm. I honestly don’t know where he might be.

Text.SourceString: Have you tried the vineyard? He could be in the greenhouse.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you tried the vineyard? He could be in the greenhouse.

Text.SourceString: We offered to let <NpcName>Ben</> stay at the house, but he turned it down.
Text.LocalizedString: We offered to let <NpcName>Ben</> stay at the house, but he turned it down.

Text.SourceString: I reckon he likes to live on his own.
Text.LocalizedString: I reckon he likes to live on his own.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Ben</> is a good friend of mine, but I still tell him some of his items are overpriced junk.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Ben</> is a good friend of mine, but I still tell him some of his items are overpriced junk.

Text.SourceString: I believe, in this instance, that honesty is the best policy.
Text.LocalizedString: I believe, in this instance, that honesty is the best policy.

Text.SourceString: There’s no better way to spend the day than being outside, especially in weather like this.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s no better way to spend the day than being outside, especially in weather like this.

Text.SourceString: There’s so much more to running a vineyard than shipping wine.//I have to maintain relationships with our buyers, which means inviting them over for dinner every once in a while.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s so much more to running a vineyard than shipping wine.//I have to maintain relationships with our buyers, which means inviting them over for dinner every once in a while.

Text.SourceString: I keep my business relationships separate from personal ones.//<portrait=normal>With good business partners, I can’t risk getting too close and damaging the relationship.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep my business relationships separate from personal ones.//<portrait=normal>With good business partners, I can’t risk getting too close and damaging the relationship.

Text.SourceString: Hmm, I think I’ll chill here today. I’m too tired to go to the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm, I think I’ll chill here today. I’m too tired to go to the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: I might go to the Tavern later. I’m craving a big plate of pasta!
Text.LocalizedString: I might go to the Tavern later. I’m craving a big plate of pasta!

Text.SourceString: Hmm, I think I’ll chill here today. I’m too tired to go to the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm, I think I’ll chill here today. I’m too tired to go to the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: Tradition is what links us to our past, and hopefully to our future as well.
Text.LocalizedString: Tradition is what links us to our past, and hopefully to our future as well.

Text.SourceString: Care for a drink, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Care for a drink, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Yesterday was all right. I took a little break from the store and did some quality control for our wine.//Had dinner with my parents. What about you? What did you do on Sunday?
Text.LocalizedString: Yesterday was all right. I took a little break from the store and did some quality control for our wine.//Had dinner with my parents. What about you? What did you do on Sunday?

Text.SourceString: Too much tension at the house sometimes.//It’s better to just walk it off or to disappear for the day altogether.
Text.LocalizedString: Too much tension at the house sometimes.//It’s better to just walk it off or to disappear for the day altogether.

Text.SourceString: I think I had too much family interaction yesterday. It was still good, but a bit exhausting. It’s a confusing feeling.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I had too much family interaction yesterday. It was still good, but a bit exhausting. It’s a confusing feeling.

Text.SourceString: Oh, perfect timing! I was preparing my lunch this morning and thought of you.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, perfect timing! I was preparing my lunch this morning and thought of you.

Text.SourceString: Maybe we can make a regular lunch date. You know how I try out new recipes every so often?//That way, you can try my cooking, and I can get your input in return.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe we can make a regular lunch date. You know how I try out new recipes every so often?//That way, you can try my cooking, and I can get your input in return.

Text.SourceString: I can’t focus on work at home.//There are always so many distractions, like <NPCName>Taco</> zooming in and out, being adorable. Very distracting.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t focus on work at home.//There are always so many distractions, like <NPCName>Taco</> zooming in and out, being adorable. Very distracting.

Text.SourceString: And then there’s Mother.
Text.LocalizedString: And then there’s Mother.

Text.SourceString: I don’t reckon living downtown is an option for me.//My parents worked hard for the vineyard, and they’ve been telling me my whole life how proud they are that I’m carrying on the family business.//Since I was in diapers, I’m sure.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t reckon living downtown is an option for me.//My parents worked hard for the vineyard, and they’ve been telling me my whole life how proud they are that I’m carrying on the family business.//Since I was in diapers, I’m sure.

Text.SourceString: It isn’t just a business for us, you see. It’s a legacy.//I knew it would break their hearts if I told them I didn’t want to live at the vineyard.//<portrait=sad>They’d take it as me not wanting the vineyard.
Text.LocalizedString: It isn’t just a business for us, you see. It’s a legacy.//I knew it would break their hearts if I told them I didn’t want to live at the vineyard.//<portrait=sad>They’d take it as me not wanting the vineyard.

Text.SourceString: I’ve confided lots of personal things to you. Sometimes, I freak myself out at night when I think about it.//<portrait=concerned>Certainly, I didn’t want to bang on your door at one in the morning to ask you this. Umm…
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve confided lots of personal things to you. Sometimes, I freak myself out at night when I think about it.//<portrait=concerned>Certainly, I didn’t want to bang on your door at one in the morning to ask you this. Umm…

Text.SourceString: But you won’t tell anyone, will you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I trust you. For some reason, I feel like I can tell you things.
Text.LocalizedString: But you won’t tell anyone, will you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I trust you. For some reason, I feel like I can tell you things.

Text.SourceString: You? A bother? Never. I actually enjoy picking your brain.//<portrait=normal>You say the most outrageous things. I love it!
Text.LocalizedString: You? A bother? Never. I actually enjoy picking your brain.//<portrait=normal>You say the most outrageous things. I love it!

Text.SourceString: No wonder you look incredible.//You do so much walking around the island, on top of that farming workout. Respect.
Text.LocalizedString: No wonder you look incredible.//You do so much walking around the island, on top of that farming workout. Respect.

Text.SourceString: By the way, I like talking to you. Sorry if I don’t always act like it.
Text.LocalizedString: By the way, I like talking to you. Sorry if I don’t always act like it.

Text.SourceString: You’re really cool. Besides, you’re one of my biggest customers. *chuckles*
Text.LocalizedString: You’re really cool. Besides, you’re one of my biggest customers. *chuckles*

Text.SourceString: I usually just hang out around town or on the beach.//<portrait=normal>Living in Hillside makes me feel like I’m out in nature every day. I have no desire to visit the lake or the forest.
Text.LocalizedString: I usually just hang out around town or on the beach.//<portrait=normal>Living in Hillside makes me feel like I’m out in nature every day. I have no desire to visit the lake or the forest.

Text.SourceString: Not an outdoorsy person, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: Not an outdoorsy person, I guess.

Text.SourceString: I’m all for lore, but some of the stuff I read is out of this world. I don’t mind it, though!//That type of thing keeps me on the edge of my seat.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m all for lore, but some of the stuff I read is out of this world. I don’t mind it, though!//That type of thing keeps me on the edge of my seat.

Text.SourceString: I could lose sleep reading about Coral Island lore. As a matter of fact, I have. Many times.
Text.LocalizedString: I could lose sleep reading about Coral Island lore. As a matter of fact, I have. Many times.

Text.SourceString: Come and hang out here more often, will you? I could use your company.
Text.LocalizedString: Come and hang out here more often, will you? I could use your company.

Text.SourceString: You’re not going to make me beg, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: You’re not going to make me beg, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: You eat raw food? Like raw eggplant?//Like not on a salad. I’m talking <Italic>raw</> raw.//<portrait=happy>Yeah? Good for you!
Text.LocalizedString: You eat raw food? Like raw eggplant?//Like not on a salad. I’m talking <Italic>raw</> raw.//<portrait=happy>Yeah? Good for you!

Text.SourceString: I never thought of myself as a relationship kind of guy.//But I can see how it could be tempting.
Text.LocalizedString: I never thought of myself as a relationship kind of guy.//But I can see how it could be tempting.

Text.SourceString: I think the key is to find someone compatible. Someone you can be friends with.
Text.LocalizedString: I think the key is to find someone compatible. Someone you can be friends with.

Text.SourceString: Our family donates to the town every year for the upkeep of the cemetery.//It’s not much, but it seems to be helping.
Text.LocalizedString: Our family donates to the town every year for the upkeep of the cemetery.//It’s not much, but it seems to be helping.

Text.SourceString: My friend <NpcName>Pablo</> and his brother usually take care of cemetery maintenance.
Text.LocalizedString: My friend <NpcName>Pablo</> and his brother usually take care of cemetery maintenance.

Text.SourceString: I’m not one to care about farming or to poke around other people’s personal lives.//But how are things with you and your farm?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not one to care about farming or to poke around other people’s personal lives.//But how are things with you and your farm?

Text.SourceString: I just want to say how much I appreciate your friendship, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>You’re one of the only people on this island I consider a close friend.
Text.LocalizedString: I just want to say how much I appreciate your friendship, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>You’re one of the only people on this island I consider a close friend.

Text.SourceString: I admire your courage moving here. It was a big change, and you went for it.
Text.LocalizedString: I admire your courage moving here. It was a big change, and you went for it.

Text.SourceString: I never really thought about settling down, I guess. I was too busy running the vineyard and making a name for myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I never really thought about settling down, I guess. I was too busy running the vineyard and making a name for myself.

Text.SourceString: But it sure wouldn’t hurt if the right person came along.
Text.LocalizedString: But it sure wouldn’t hurt if the right person came along.

Text.SourceString: It’s great that the store is downtown. That’s where most of the traffic is.//<portrait=normal>We’d probably never be able to get a permit for an electronics store anywhere else, anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s great that the store is downtown. That’s where most of the traffic is.//<portrait=normal>We’d probably never be able to get a permit for an electronics store anywhere else, anyway.

Text.SourceString: The store also gives me a reason to take a good three- to four-hour walk two or three days a week.//My doctor likes that.
Text.LocalizedString: The store also gives me a reason to take a good three- to four-hour walk two or three days a week.//My doctor likes that.

Text.SourceString: Oh! You like my hair? Thank you. You caught me off guard with the compliment.//Then I’ll keep my hair like this forever. You look magnificent yourself.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! You like my hair? Thank you. You caught me off guard with the compliment.//Then I’ll keep my hair like this forever. You look magnificent yourself.

Text.SourceString: No need to thank me, it’s true!
Text.LocalizedString: No need to thank me, it’s true!

Text.SourceString: You’re always so kind to me. I consider us close friends.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re always so kind to me. I consider us close friends.

Text.SourceString: All is good, then. I’m glad for both of us.
Text.LocalizedString: All is good, then. I’m glad for both of us.

Special.SourceString: I consider us good friends too.
Special.LocalizedString: I consider us good friends too.

239.SpecialTag: I consider us good friends too.
239.Question: R1

Text.SourceString: All is good, then. I’m glad!
Text.LocalizedString: All is good, then. I’m glad!

Text.SourceString: Er, you look magnificent today.
Text.LocalizedString: Er, you look magnificent today.

Special.SourceString: That’s it? You don’t think I’m cute or something?
Special.LocalizedString: That’s it? You don’t think I’m cute or something?

241.SpecialTag: That’s it? You don’t think I’m cute or something?
241.Question: R3

Text.SourceString: I wish we could just drop everything and go away for the weekend.//<portrait=blushing>Maybe a weekend sail. Just you and me at sea. How does that sound?
Text.LocalizedString: I wish we could just drop everything and go away for the weekend.//<portrait=blushing>Maybe a weekend sail. Just you and me at sea. How does that sound?

Text.SourceString: Unless you wouldn’t like that, of course. The choice is yours, as always.
Text.LocalizedString: Unless you wouldn’t like that, of course. The choice is yours, as always.

Text.SourceString: We’re standing so close to each other. Umm…
Text.LocalizedString: We’re standing so close to each other. Umm…

Text.SourceString: Please forgive my heart. It’s pounding very loudly, very rude. I can’t help it. You’re making me nervous.
Text.LocalizedString: Please forgive my heart. It’s pounding very loudly, very rude. I can’t help it. You’re making me nervous.

Text.SourceString: Growing up here, away from any big city, I had a hard time finding electronic toys or even the TV I wanted.//I know it sounds so shallow, but it bugged me.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing up here, away from any big city, I had a hard time finding electronic toys or even the TV I wanted.//I know it sounds so shallow, but it bugged me.

Text.SourceString: I thought to myself, why not buy the things I like in bulk and see if others like them too?//<portrait=happy>It turned out they do. People appreciate not having to order their electronics themselves and wait for them to arrive. So, here we are.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought to myself, why not buy the things I like in bulk and see if others like them too?//<portrait=happy>It turned out they do. People appreciate not having to order their electronics themselves and wait for them to arrive. So, here we are.

Text.SourceString: So busy today. I have so many orders to process.
Text.LocalizedString: So busy today. I have so many orders to process.

Text.SourceString: You don’t always have to visit me here, <PlayerName>$player</>.//You’re welcome at the vineyard. We could talk and chill over a snack or dinner, perhaps.
Text.LocalizedString: You don’t always have to visit me here, <PlayerName>$player</>.//You’re welcome at the vineyard. We could talk and chill over a snack or dinner, perhaps.

Text.SourceString: My mother cooks very well. I’d offer to cook for you, but I’m afraid you might be offended by my cooking.
Text.LocalizedString: My mother cooks very well. I’d offer to cook for you, but I’m afraid you might be offended by my cooking.

Text.SourceString: Someday, I’ll have to take over this place, focus on the vineyard, and put my personal goals aside.//I’m not too happy about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Someday, I’ll have to take over this place, focus on the vineyard, and put my personal goals aside.//I’m not too happy about it.

Text.SourceString: But it’s just a fact I have to live with.
Text.LocalizedString: But it’s just a fact I have to live with.

Text.SourceString: I caught <NPCName>Theo</> singing in the rain the other day. Like, why?//<portrait=concerned>Creative people, huh? They’re hard to understand sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I caught <NPCName>Theo</> singing in the rain the other day. Like, why?//<portrait=concerned>Creative people, huh? They’re hard to understand sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I have to order some things from <NPCName>Sam</>’s. I need several imported things, like garlic jam.//<portrait=concerned>They don’t make it here.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to order some things from <NPCName>Sam</>’s. I need several imported things, like garlic jam.//<portrait=concerned>They don’t make it here.

Text.SourceString: Have you read this book? I picked it up on the way here.//Got it from the library. It looks well read. Must be popular.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you read this book? I picked it up on the way here.//Got it from the library. It looks well read. Must be popular.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to have a dip in the water soon. Cool off a bit.//<portrait=normal>You should join me!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to have a dip in the water soon. Cool off a bit.//<portrait=normal>You should join me!

Text.SourceString: Watching an old film on <NpcName>Pablo’s</> setup is something else.//<portrait=happy>It’s the best place see a film in Starlet Town. Not even I have a setup like his.
Text.LocalizedString: Watching an old film on <NpcName>Pablo’s</> setup is something else.//<portrait=happy>It’s the best place see a film in Starlet Town. Not even I have a setup like his.

Text.SourceString: It’s warm now. I don’t need my sweater.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s warm now. I don’t need my sweater.

Text.SourceString: May I offer you my jacket?//<portrait=happy>Oh, all right, then. Just let me know if you need an extra layer.
Text.LocalizedString: May I offer you my jacket?//<portrait=happy>Oh, all right, then. Just let me know if you need an extra layer.
